elix\":\"not 100% sure what you mean, you can have multiple agents on the platform but it is mainly a 1-1 contact platform, rather than multiparty conference\"},{\"Customer\":\"I mean that lets say I have two agents, they can both access the portal and manage/connect to users who are looking to video chat\"},{\"Felix\":\"yes\"},{\"Felix\":\"although it\'s inbound rather than outbound. so the agents are waiting on app/website users to initiate the chat\"},{\"Customer\":\"Yh but agents can see who is waiting and connect to them via the dashboard/portal?\"},{\"Felix\":\"unfortunately not. that is roadmap for web but im not sure if that would be possible with the app. the system is currently built with the idea of a contact centre type flow where the system allocates interctions to agents\"},{\"Customer\":\"I\'m a bit confused. Do you have a contact number so we could possibly discuss this on call maybe?\"},{\"Felix\":\"sure i am on <phoneNumber>\"},{\"Felix\":\"can we do the call at midday if that works? or 1145?\"},{\"Customer\":\"So you\'re not free now?\"},{\"Felix\":\"sure i can do now\"},{\"Customer\":\"perfect\"},{\"Customer\":\"<email>\"}]');
